    "recap_url": "https://www.upstatespartans.com/news/2026/3/10/maloy-heaghneys-three-run-triple-lifts-baseball-to-5-2-crosstown-rivalry-series-over-wofford-at-fifth-third-park",
    "recap_headline": "University of South Carolina Upstate Athletics",
    "recap_text": "SPARTANBURG, S.C. \u2013\nReturning to the park it helped open last April, USC Upstate baseball put itself back in the win column, downing its crosstown rival Wofford Tuesday evening at Fifth Third Park, the home of the Hub City Spartanburgers. The Spartans captured victory by a 5-2 score, incidentally a reverse of the final margin of last season's game at the venue.\nStriking first, Upstate put a run on the board in the first following a pair of leadoff hits from redshirt sophomore centerfield\nHenry Zenor\nand redshirt senior third baseman\nJake Armsey\n. Zenor crossed as the Terriers turned a double play, marking the first run of the ballgame. Seeing the first two batters of the following frame reach, the Spartans' sacrifice's a sac bunt from senior second baseman\nGage Griggs\nand a sac fly from redshirt sophomore rightfielder\nKenan Bowman\npushed across the team's second tally.\nWofford fought back, scratching two in the fourth to knot the ball. However, the Spartans remained unfazed, loading the bases in the fifth before redshirt sophomore shortstop\nMaloy Heaghney\ndelivered the biggest hit of the night, a bases-clearing triple to the alley in right-center.\nLocking down the win, Upstate's bullpen proved nails as redshirt freshman right-handed pitcher\nJacob Kirby\nand senior righty\nReece Hemmerling\ncombined for 5.0 innings of scoreless relief. Kirby worked 3.0 shutout innings, earning his second win of the season while Hemmerling offered 2.0 scoreless frames for his first career save.\nGame Information\nScore: USC Upstate 5; Wofford 2\nRecords: USC Upstate (8-10; 0-0 Big South); Wofford (10-6; 0-0 SoCon)\nLocation: Fifth Third Park | Spartanburg, S.C.\nHow It Happened\nB1: Seeing the first two batters reach via base hit, Upstate scratched the first run of the game as\nHenry Zenor\ncrossed the plate as Wofford turned a double play.\nB2: Utilizing a pair of sacrifices, a sac bunt from\nGage Griggs\nand a sac fly from\nKenan Bowman\n, the Spartans plated the game's second run in the second.\nT4: Behind three straight singles and a squeeze bunt, Wofford fought back to tie the game, scoring two in the fourth behind RBI from Andrew Mannelly and Hunter Hendon.\nB5: Stepping to the plate with the bases loaded and two outs,\nMaloy Heaghney\nsplit the gap in right-center, clearing the bases with a triple.\nNotable\nOffering his bases-clearing triple,\nMaloy Heaghney\nrecorded his team-lead-tying third multi-RBI game of the season. With three RBI Wednesday, he's the only Spartan to record three-plus RBI on three separate occasions.\nWorking 2.0 scoreless innings to earn his first career save,\nReece Hemmerling\nnotched his third straight scoreless outing in the past week. Since pitching against South Carolina last Tuesday, he's pitched 5.2 consecutive scoreless frames.\nUp Next for the Spartans\nBeginning a new season as it returns to Cleveland S. Harley Park, USC Upstate begins Big South Conference play this weekend, welcoming High Point for a three-game set and a rematch of last season's Big South Championship Game. The series begins Friday with a 3 p.m. ET first pitch.\nConnect with the Spartans\nFacebook.com/UpstateAthletics\nTwitter | @UpstateBSB | @UpstateSpartans\nInstagram | @UpstateBSB | @UpstateSpartans\nYouTube.com/UpstateSpartans\nINVEST IN CHAMPIONS\n- Join the Upstate Athletic Fund (UAF) and enjoy enhanced benefits for your support of all USC Upstate programs! Make your gift today,\nclick here\n!"
